<h2>Email Marketing: ConvertKit ($79/mo for our list size)</h2>

<p><strong>What it replaced:</strong> Mailchimp ($99/mo, worse deliverability, clunky automations).</p>

ConvertKit handles our partner newsletter, lead nurture sequences, and broadcast emails. The tagging system is genuinely excellent -- we tag partners by tier, location type, and onboarding stage, then send targeted sequences based on tags.

The automation is cleaner than anything else I've used at this price point. Sequences are visual, logic-based, and easy to edit without breaking things.

<p><strong>Would I recommend it?</strong> Yes, across the board. It's the right email platform for operators building lists from 0 to 50,000 subscribers.</p>

