<h2>Network Management: Ubiquiti UniFi (Hardware + $0/mo cloud)</h2>

<p><strong>What it replaced:</strong> Consumer routers at venue locations ($15–$40/device, unmanageable at scale).</p>

We deploy Ubiquiti UniFi access points at every our partner venue. The UniFi Network app is free -- no subscription -- and lets us manage all access points, create SSID configurations, monitor usage, and push firmware updates from one dashboard.

For WiFi data offloading specifically, Ubiquiti is the only choice that gives us the RADIUS authentication and captive portal flexibility we need to create the SYH (AT&T) and SYX (T-Mobile) certificate networks at scale.

<p><strong>Hardware cost:</strong> $129–$299/AP depending on model. Ongoing cost: $0 for cloud management (with UniFi Cloud Key or self-hosted controller).</p>

